# Typography

For **size and scale tokens**, see [ui-scale.mdc](Mobile/.cursor/rules/ui-scale.mdc).

## Source of truth

| Dimension | Location | Profiled? |
|-----------|----------|-----------|
| **Typeface** | `text/font/types.ts`, `text/font/profiles/*`, `FONT_PROFILES` | Yes (`Auto`, `Roboto`, …) |
| **Style** | `text/style/index.ts`, `TEXT_STYLE` | No — fixed per role |

- **`TextProvider`** ([`context/TextContext.tsx`](Mobile/context/TextContext.tsx)) exposes the active UI scale + font profile pair and fixed `TEXT_STYLE`.
- **Colors** stay in [`useColorTheme()`](Mobile/context/ColorThemeContext.tsx) — never in text/style constants.

## Role categories

Shared keys between `style` and font profiles (via `fontSlot`):

`preview`, `betaSection`, `pageScreen`, `filter`, `map`, `button`, `toast`, `regionScreen`, `infoScreen`

## Using text in components

Always pass **`size` + `typography`** together into `ConstantText` / `ScalingText` / `ScalingTextGroup`. Read `size` from `useText().uiScale` and `typography` from `useText().style`.

### Constant text

```tsx
import { ConstantText } from "@/components/text/ConstantText";
import { useText } from "@/context/typography/TextContext";
import { useColorTheme } from "@/context/theme/ColorThemeContext";

export function ExampleTitle() {
  const { uiScale, style } = useText();
  const { text } = useColorTheme();
  return (
    <ConstantText
      size={uiScale.pageScreen.text.title}
      typography={style.pageScreen.title}
      style={{ color: text.primary }}
    >
      Title
    </ConstantText>
  );
}
```

### Scaling text

```tsx
import { ScalingText } from "@/components/text/ScalingText";
import { useText } from "@/context/typography/TextContext";

export function ExampleLabel({ label }: { label: string }) {
  const { uiScale, style } = useText();
  return (
    <ScalingText
      size={uiScale.filter.buttons.checkbox.text!}
      typography={style.filter.optionLabel}
      numberOfLines={1}
      measure={{ type: "width" }}
    >
      {label}
    </ScalingText>
  );
}
```

### Non-`Text` APIs (Mapbox, `TextInput`, HTML)

Use uiScale resolvers for pixel sizes; typography still from `style`. See ui-scale rule.

Always set `allowFontScaling={false}` on token-driven text.

## Do's

- Read tokens from `useText()` (`uiScale`, `style`, `font`).
- Pass **`size` + `typography`** together.
- Apply **colors** from `useColorTheme()` via the `style` prop.
- Add new typography to `text/style/types.ts` and `text/style/index.ts`; add matching size tokens per ui-scale rule.

## Don'ts

- Do not hardcode `fontSize`, `fontWeight`, or `fontFamily` in component StyleSheets.
- Do not put colors in text/style constants.
- Do not use raw `Text` for app copy unless rendering HTML or a one-off nested span inside `renderLabel`.

## Adding a font profile

1. Add `FontProfileKey` in `constants/text/font/types.ts`.
2. Create `constants/text/font/profiles/<name>.ts`.
3. Register in `FONT_PROFILES`.
4. Add font files to `assets/fonts/` and register via the `expo-font` config plugin in `app.json`; use each file's PostScript name as `fontFamily` (e.g. `Roboto-Regular`, not `Roboto_400Regular`); rebuild native app.

## Adding typography for a new role

1. Extend the category type in `text/style/types.ts`.
2. Add `TypographySpec` entry in `text/style/index.ts`.
3. Add matching size tokens in uiScale (see ui-scale rule).
4. Wire the component with `ConstantText` or `ScalingText`.
